<title>USA: Verity merges with Cognisoft, sees charge.</title>
<headline>Verity merges with Cognisoft, sees charge.</headline>
<dateline>SUNNYVALE, Calif. 1997-01-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Verity Inc said Monday it has agreed to merge with privately held Cognisoft Corp and take a $10 million charge against third quarter earnings for the deal.</p>
<p>Verity, which provides search and retrieval technology for the Internet and Intranet, said it is paying $10 million cash for Cognisoft.</p>
<p>Cognisoft was founded in 1996 by five former Microsoft managers and has focused on developing an Intranet application called IntelliServ, Verity said.</p>
<p>Verity said the deal should close by week's end.</p>
